00:24:02.999 --> 00:24:04.540
Now, there's a few
components of this

00:24:04.540 --> 00:24:05.350
that I want to walk you through.

00:24:05.350 --> 00:24:06.760
The first one is very simple.

00:24:06.760 --> 00:24:09.359
Let's go play a level.

00:24:09.359 --> 00:24:11.650
And if we were building this
game in a traditional way,

00:24:11.650 --> 00:24:13.330
we would have built
these levels beforehand.

00:24:13.330 --> 00:24:15.621
We would have rolled them up
into the data of our game.

00:24:15.621 --> 00:24:17.080
And we would have
shipped it out.

00:24:17.080 --> 00:24:18.910
But with Firebase,
we have the ability

00:24:18.910 --> 00:24:22.030
to really easily store this
information inside of Firebase.

00:24:22.030 --> 00:24:24.760
So these levels are all stored
in the Firebase real time

00:24:24.760 --> 00:24:25.819
database.

00:24:25.819 --> 00:24:27.610
So as I go through
here, and I roll around,

00:24:27.610 --> 00:24:31.100
and I try to get to the
end very, very well.

00:24:31.100 --> 00:24:33.220
So it looks like I'm
great at this game.

00:24:33.220 --> 00:24:35.990
I know that this level is coming
out of the real time database.

00:24:35.990 --> 00:24:38.419
So if I wanted to add levels,
or I wanted to tweak levels,

00:24:38.419 --> 00:24:40.210
I wouldn't have to
redeploy play this game.

00:24:40.210 --> 00:24:42.293
I could just go out, and
I could edit these levels

00:24:42.293 --> 00:24:43.390
in my database.

00:24:43.390 --> 00:24:44.740
And they'll get pulled down.

00:24:44.740 --> 00:24:47.290
Similarly, if I want
to record high scores,

00:24:47.290 --> 00:24:49.340
I can submit the
score, upload it.

00:24:49.340 --> 00:24:50.940
It turns out I did
not do very well,

00:24:50.940 --> 00:24:52.439
so I only got five
seconds on there.

00:24:52.439 --> 00:24:54.680
But this is also stored
in the real time database.

00:24:54.680 --> 00:24:57.084
So this isn't a crazy new
idea, but it's something

00:24:57.084 --> 00:24:58.750
that generally you
would have had to put

00:24:58.750 --> 00:24:59.833
effort in the servers for.

00:24:59.833 --> 00:25:02.290
You would have had to put
effort into infrastructure.

00:25:02.290 --> 00:25:04.502
And with Firebase, you
just don't have to.

00:25:04.502 --> 00:25:05.960
There's some other
great use cases.

00:25:05.960 --> 00:25:07.780
So since we know
all of our levels

00:25:07.780 --> 00:25:09.826
are stored in the
real time database,

00:25:09.826 --> 00:25:11.200
we can go a step
further and say,

00:25:11.200 --> 00:25:13.660
why don't we just let
people make new levels?

00:25:13.660 --> 00:25:18.030
So we'll go into the editor,
and we'll design up a level.

00:25:18.030 --> 00:25:21.610
It's going to say A for Abe.

00:25:21.610 --> 00:25:23.825
Ab is close enough to Ab.

00:25:23.825 --> 00:25:27.410
We'll put that there,
put an exit over here.

00:25:27.410 --> 00:25:27.910
There we go.

00:25:27.910 --> 00:25:31.460
Let's play that, make
sure that it works.

00:25:31.460 --> 00:25:33.680
Beautiful, great level,
we'll go back to our editor.

00:25:33.680 --> 00:25:36.140
Now we have the ability
to save, share this level,

00:25:36.140 --> 00:25:38.690
send it around, and it's
all stored in the real time

00:25:38.690 --> 00:25:39.900
database.

00:25:39.900 --> 00:25:42.091
Once we get into
saving and sharing,

00:25:42.091 --> 00:25:44.340
we start getting into other
Firebase features, though.

00:25:44.340 --> 00:25:48.470
So Ab is going to be
the name of that map.

00:25:48.470 --> 00:25:49.970
As soon as I upload
this, it's going

00:25:49.970 --> 00:25:52.170
to get published to everyone
who wants to know about it.

00:25:52.170 --> 00:25:53.836
So we're sending out
push notifications.

00:25:53.836 --> 00:25:55.820
We won't get one on
this device, but if you

00:25:55.820 --> 00:25:57.903
had this game installed,
you'd get a thing saying,

00:25:57.903 --> 00:26:00.080
hey, new level has been
released on Mecha Hampster.

00:26:00.080 --> 00:26:01.340
You can go play that.

00:26:01.340 --> 00:26:03.620
If I want, I can click
share, and I can share it out

00:26:03.620 --> 00:26:05.930
to a bunch of different
friends and people like that.

00:26:05.930 --> 00:26:08.060
I sadly have no
friends on this device,

00:26:08.060 --> 00:26:10.010
but if I had recent
contacts, they'd

00:26:10.010 --> 00:26:11.910
be showing up down there.

00:26:11.910 --> 00:26:18.600
Then we can just go ahead and
head back to our main level,

00:26:18.600 --> 00:26:21.690
and we can let people
experience that gain.

00:26:21.690 --> 00:26:24.180
So these are things-- like
I said, this isn't crazy.

00:26:24.180 --> 00:26:26.110
It's not anything ridiculous.

00:26:26.110 --> 00:26:28.035
It's just easier
for you, and it's

00:26:28.035 --> 00:26:30.780
less effort for you to
maintain this game over time.

00:26:30.780 --> 00:26:32.274
It gets taken care
of by Firebase.

00:26:32.274 --> 00:26:34.440
And if something does go
down, if one of the servers

00:26:34.440 --> 00:26:36.810
falls over or
anything like that,

00:26:36.810 --> 00:26:41.520
we know that it's going
to come back to Firebase

00:26:41.520 --> 00:26:42.840
to take care of that.

00:26:42.840 --> 00:26:45.569
And it's just a nicer
way to build an app.

00:26:45.569 --> 00:26:47.610
So real quick, let's just
recap what we just saw.

00:26:47.610 --> 00:26:50.160
So we sign in with
Firebase authentication.

00:26:50.160 --> 00:26:51.300
Obviously, no one noticed.

00:26:51.300 --> 00:26:52.800
The player doesn't
notice that we're

00:26:52.800 --> 00:26:53.940
using Firebase authentication.

00:26:53.940 --> 00:26:55.110
They just know they
made an account.

00:26:55.110 --> 00:26:55.860
They made a level.

00:26:55.860 --> 00:26:56.790
That's great.

00:26:56.790 --> 00:26:59.040
Then we use a real time
database to load levels,

00:26:59.040 --> 00:27:00.990
to create a level.

00:27:00.990 --> 00:27:03.510
We use cloud messaging to
send out push notifications

00:27:03.510 --> 00:27:05.100
to everyone who cared.

00:27:05.100 --> 00:27:07.950
And we used Firebase Analytics
to record all of this,

00:27:07.950 --> 00:27:10.566
so we know what
everyone is doing.

00:27:10.566 --> 00:27:11.940
All of this with
without servers,

00:27:11.940 --> 00:27:13.398
all of this without
infrastructure,

00:27:13.398 --> 00:27:15.300
and without cloud,
and everything

00:27:15.300 --> 00:27:17.250
like that that you don't
want to think about.

00:27:17.250 --> 00:27:20.880
All we did as a developer
is include our SDK in there,

00:27:20.880 --> 00:27:26.160
call out to some services,
and let Firebase do its magic.

00:27:26.160 --> 00:27:29.430
So this whole section
is who is Firebase for,

00:27:29.430 --> 00:27:31.620
and the answer is
Firebase is for anyone,

00:27:31.620 --> 00:27:33.630
any game, big or small.

00:27:33.630 --> 00:27:36.300
There's always something in
here that's going to be useful.

00:27:36.300 --> 00:27:38.140
And we looked at that
gigantic chart of all

00:27:38.140 --> 00:27:39.181
these different features.

00:27:39.181 --> 00:27:42.390
And what it comes down to is
that any one of those features

00:27:42.390 --> 00:27:45.570
could be useful to you, but
in all likelihood, all of them

00:27:45.570 --> 00:27:46.470
won't be.

00:27:46.470 --> 00:27:49.990
You won't want to put in all
15 features into your game.

00:27:49.990 --> 00:27:52.380
So if we're forcing you to
include a gigantic SDK you're

00:27:52.380 --> 00:27:55.505
not going to use, it's not going
to be in your best interests.

00:27:55.505 --> 00:27:57.630
So if you only want to use
Firebase authentication,

00:27:57.630 --> 00:27:59.430
if you only want
to use analytics,

00:27:59.430 --> 00:28:02.640
you can drop that in
independent of dynamic links

00:28:02.640 --> 00:28:03.990
or remote config.

00:28:03.990 --> 00:28:06.570
You don't have to deal with
those if you don't want to.

00:28:06.570 --> 00:28:09.060
Obviously, you can, and they
all work better together.

00:28:09.060 --> 00:28:11.040
But every individual
component of Firebase

00:28:11.040 --> 00:28:13.740
is designed to be used
alone with the addition

00:28:13.740 --> 00:28:18.720
of the Firebase core,
which is the shared bits.

